#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.35"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.35:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.35:0.2"
msgid "4. Devadūtavagga"
msgstr "4. Messengers of the Gods"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.35:0.3"
msgid "35. Hatthakasutta"
msgstr "35. With Hatthaka"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "an3.35:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "an3.35:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā āḷaviyaṃ viharati gomagge siṃsapāvane paṇṇasanthare."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Āḷavī, on a mat of leaves by a cow-"
"path in a grove of Indian Rosewood."

msgctxt "an3.35:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho hatthako āḷavako jaṅghāvihāraṃ anucaṅkamamāno anuvicaramāno addasa "
"bhagavantaṃ gomagge siṃsapāvane paṇṇasanthare nisinnaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then as Hatthaka of Āḷavī was going for a walk he saw the Buddha sitting on "
"that mat of leaves."

msgctxt "an3.35:1.4"
msgid ""
"Disvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā "
"ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho hatthako āḷavako bhagavantaṃ "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"He went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to the "
"Buddha:"

msgctxt "an3.35:1.5"
msgid "“kacci, bhante bhagavā, sukhamasayitthā”ti?"
msgstr "“Sir, I trust the Buddha slept well?”"

msgctxt "an3.35:1.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, kumāra, sukhamasayitthaṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, prince, I slept well."

msgctxt "an3.35:1.7"
msgid "Ye ca pana loke sukhaṃ senti, ahaṃ tesaṃ aññataro”ti."
msgstr "I am one of those who sleep well in the world.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.137"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.35:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Sītā, bhante, hemantikā ratti, antaraṭṭhako himapātasamayo, kharā "
"gokaṇṭakahatā bhūmi, tanuko paṇṇasantharo, viraḷāni rukkhassa pattāni, "
"sītāni kāsāyāni vatthāni, sīto ca verambho vāto vāyati."
msgstr ""
"“The winter nights are cold, sir, and it’s the week of mid-winter, when the "
"snow falls. Rough is the ground trampled under the cows’ hooves, and thin is "
"the mat of leaves. The leaves are sparse on the trees, the ocher robes are "
"cold, and cold blows the north wind."

msgctxt "an3.35:2.2"
msgid "Atha ca pana bhagavā evamāha:"
msgstr "And yet the Buddha says:"

msgctxt "an3.35:2.3"
msgid "‘evaṃ, kumāra, sukhamasayitthaṃ."
msgstr "‘Yes, prince, I slept well."

msgctxt "an3.35:2.4"
msgid "Ye ca pana loke sukhaṃ senti, ahaṃ tesaṃ aññataro’”ti."
msgstr "I am one of those who sleep well in the world.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.35:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Tena hi, kumāra, taññevettha paṭipucchissāmi. Yathā te khameyya tathā naṃ "
"byākareyyāsi."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, prince, I’ll ask you about this in return, and you can answer as "
"you like."

msgctxt "an3.35:3.2"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, kumāra, idhassa gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā "
"kūṭāgāraṃ ullittāvalittaṃ nivātaṃ phusitaggaḷaṃ pihitavātapānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"What do you think? Take the case of a householder or his son, who lives in a "
"bungalow, plastered inside and out, draft-free, with latches fastened and "
"windows shuttered."

#. VAR: kadalimigapavarapaccattharaṇo → kādalimigapavarapaccattharaṇo (bj)
msgctxt "an3.35:3.3"
msgid ""
"Tatrassa pallaṅko gonakatthato paṭikatthato paṭalikatthato "
"kadalimigapavarapaccattharaṇo sauttaracchado ubhato lohitakūpadhāno;"
msgstr ""
"His couch is spread with woolen covers—shag-piled, pure white, or "
"embroidered with flowers—and spread with a fine deer hide. It has a canopy "
"above and red pillows at both ends."

#. VAR: jhāyeyya → jāleyya (mr)
msgctxt "an3.35:3.4"
msgid "telappadīpo cettha jhāyeyya;"
msgstr "An oil lamp is burning there,"

#. VAR: catasso ca → catasso (s1-3) | tasseva (mr)
msgctxt "an3.35:3.5"
msgid "catasso ca pajāpatiyo manāpāmanāpena paccupaṭṭhitā assu."
msgstr "while his four wives attend to him in all manner of pleasing ways."

msgctxt "an3.35:3.6"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, kumāra, sukhaṃ vā so sayeyya no vā?"
msgstr "What do you think, prince, would he sleep well, or not?"

msgctxt "an3.35:3.7"
msgid "Kathaṃ vā te ettha hotī”ti?"
msgstr "Or how do you see this?”"

msgctxt "an3.35:3.8"
msgid "“Sukhaṃ so, bhante, sayeyya."
msgstr "“He would sleep well, sir."

msgctxt "an3.35:3.9"
msgid "Ye ca pana loke sukhaṃ senti, so tesaṃ aññataro”ti."
msgstr "Of those who sleep well in the world, he would be one.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.35:4.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, kumāra, "
msgstr "“What do you think, prince? "

msgctxt "an3.35:4.2"
msgid ""
"api nu tassa gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā uppajjeyyuṃ rāgajā pariḷāhā "
"kāyikā vā cetasikā vā yehi so rāgajehi pariḷāhehi pariḍayhamāno dukkhaṃ "
"sayeyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Is it not possible that a fever born of greed—physical or mental—might arise "
"in that householder or householder’s son, burning him so he sleeps badly?”"

msgctxt "an3.35:4.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.35:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Yehi kho so, kumāra, gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā rāgajehi pariḷāhehi "
"pariḍayhamāno dukkhaṃ sayeyya, so rāgo tathāgatassa pahīno ucchinnamūlo "
"tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṅkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo."
msgstr ""
"“The greed that burns that householder or householder’s son, making them "
"sleep badly, has been cut off at the root by the Realized One, made like a "
"palm stump, obliterated, and unable to arise in the future."

msgctxt "an3.35:5.2"
msgid "Tasmāhaṃ sukhamasayitthaṃ."
msgstr "That’s why I sleep well."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an3.35:6.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, kumāra, "
msgstr "What do you think, prince? "

msgctxt "an3.35:6.2"
msgid ""
"api nu tassa gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā uppajjeyyuṃ dosajā pariḷāhā …"
" pe …"
msgstr "Is it not possible that a fever born of hate …"

msgctxt "an3.35:6.3"
msgid ""
"mohajā pariḷāhā kāyikā vā cetasikā vā yehi so mohajehi pariḷāhehi "
"pariḍayhamāno dukkhaṃ sayeyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"or a fever born of delusion—physical or mental—might arise in that "
"householder or householder’s son, burning him so he sleeps badly?”"

msgctxt "an3.35:6.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.138"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an3.35:7.1"
msgid ""
"“Ye hi kho so, kumāra, gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā mohajehi pariḷāhehi "
"pariḍayhamāno dukkhaṃ sayeyya, so moho tathāgatassa pahīno ucchinnamūlo "
"tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṅkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo."
msgstr ""
"“The delusion that burns that householder or householder’s son, making them "
"sleep badly, has been cut off at the root by the Realized One, made like a "
"palm stump, obliterated, and unable to arise in the future."

msgctxt "an3.35:7.2"
msgid "Tasmāhaṃ sukhamasayitthanti."
msgstr "That’s why I sleep well.”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an3.35:8.1"
msgid "Sabbadā ve sukhaṃ seti,"
msgstr "“A brahmin who is fully extinguished"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.35:8.2"
msgid "brāhmaṇo parinibbuto;"
msgstr "always sleeps well."

#. <br>
#. VAR: limpati → lippati (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an3.35:8.3"
msgid "Yo na limpati kāmesu,"
msgstr "Sensual pleasures slide off them,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.35:8.4"
msgid "sītibhūto nirūpadhi."
msgstr "they’re cooled, free of attachments."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an3.35:9.1"
msgid "Sabbā āsattiyo chetvā,"
msgstr "Since they’ve cut off all clinging,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.35:9.2"
msgid "vineyya hadaye daraṃ;"
msgstr "and removed the stress from the heart,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.35:9.3"
msgid "Upasanto sukhaṃ seti,"
msgstr "the peaceful sleep well,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.35:9.4"
msgid "santiṃ pappuyya cetaso”ti."
msgstr "abiding in peace of mind.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.35:9.5"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
